t = function(df, sample) {
  
  parameters = c()
  programs = c()
  for (i in colnames(df)) {
    if (!(grepl('programs', i)) & ('label' != i)) {
      parameters = rbind(parameters, i)
    }
    
    else{
      programs = rbind(programs, i)
    }
  }
  
  sample_parameters = c()
  for (i in parameters) {
    if (!is.na(sample[, c(i)])) {
      sample_parameters = rbind(sample_parameters, i)
    }
  }
  
  # removing programs which the candidate already did
  cols = which(select(sample, programs) == 1)
  if (length(cols) > 0) {
    df = df[, -cols]
    p = programs[c(which(select(sample, programs) == 1))]
    p = paste(p, collapse = ", ")
    p = gsub("programs_", "", p)
    writeLines(paste('---- programs which the given candidate already did ---- \n ', p))
    programs = programs[-c(which(select(sample, programs) == 1))]
  }
  
  else{
    writeLines('---- the given candidate didnt did any program yet  ----  ' )
  }
  
  a = TRUE
  b = FALSE
  droped_parameters = c()
  while ((a == TRUE) | (b == FALSE)) {
    droped_parameters = rbind(droped_parameters,sample_parameters[length(sample_parameters)])
    sample_parameters = sample_parameters[-length(sample_parameters)]
    filtered_df = semi_join(df, sample, by = sample_parameters, copy = FALSE)
    
    a = any(table(filtered_df$label) < 20)
    b = dim(filtered_df)[1] > 100
  }
  writeLines('\nparameters which removed in order to fit the given 
candidate and the limitation we defined in the function
(min number of samples and min number of samples per each lable) :\n')
  print(droped_parameters)

  
  
  ## create tree
  colnames(filtered_df)
  df_prepered_for_tree = filtered_df[, programs]
  
  # find the min label in order to create equal samples from all labels
  min_label =  min(summary(factor(df_prepered_for_tree$label)))
  
  # pulling sampels with higher programs number from each label.
  v = df_prepered_for_tree[0:0, ]
  
  for (i in c(1, 2, 3, 4)) {
    s = which(df_prepered_for_tree$label == i)
    d = df_prepered_for_tree[s, ]
    d = d[order(-d$number_of_programs), ]
    a = d[c(1:min_label - 1), ]
    v = rbind(v, a)
  }
  
  df_prepered_for_tree = v
  
  # factorization of columns:
  for (i in 1:ncol(df_prepered_for_tree)) {
    df_prepered_for_tree[, i] <- as.factor(df_prepered_for_tree[, i])
  }
  
  df_prepered_for_tree = as.data.frame(df_prepered_for_tree)
  df_prepered_for_tree = df_prepered_for_tree[,-which(names(df_prepered_for_tree) == "number_of_programs")]
  
  # function which revers strings oreder in vector
  strReverse <- function(x)
    sapply(lapply(strsplit(x, NULL), rev), paste, collapse = "")
  
  # apply function and remove unnecessary strings
  colnames(df_prepered_for_tree) = gsub("programs_", "", colnames(df_prepered_for_tree))
  colnames(df_prepered_for_tree) = strReverse(colnames(df_prepered_for_tree))
  
  fit <- rpart(
    lebal ~ .,
    data = df_prepered_for_tree,
    method = 'class',
    control = list(minsplit = 5, maxdepth = 10)
  )
  
  df_summary = sqldf(
    'select label,
             avg(days_diff) days_avg,
             median(days_diff) days_median,
             min(days_diff) min_diff,
             max(days_diff) max_diff

      from filtered_df
      where days_diff >= 0
                      group by 1'
  )
  
  writeLines(paste('\n\nthe results based on' , min_label * 4, 'sampels\n'))
  writeLines('---- time differences summary ----\n')
  print(df_summary)
  rpart.plot(fit,legend.x=0, legend.y=1.08)
  
  return (fit)
}
